# Complexity Management (CodeScene Gates)

## Hard complexity limits — CI fails above these

| Metric | Limit | Enforcement |
|---|---|---|
| Cyclomatic complexity per function | 8 | `golangci-lint` (gocyclo), `pylint` (C901) |
| Cognitive complexity per function | 10 | `golangci-lint` (gocognit), `ruff` |
| Lines per function | 40 | `golangci-lint` (funlen) |
| Lines per file | 400 | `golangci-lint` (cyclop), `wc -l` gate |
| Function parameters | 4 | custom lint rule |
| Nesting depth | 3 | manual review + `cyclop` |
| Code duplication (clone detection) | 0 clones >10 lines | CodeScene clone detection |

## The guard clause pattern — eliminate nesting

```go
// WRONG — 4 levels of nesting; cognitive complexity ~12
func processRequest(r *http.Request) error {
    if r != nil {
        if r.Body != nil {
            var req CreateRequest
            if err := json.Decode(r.Body, &req); err == nil {
                if req.Name != "" {
                    return doWork(req)
                }
            }
        }
    }
    return ErrInvalidRequest
}

// RIGHT — flat with guard clauses; cognitive complexity ~4
func processRequest(r *http.Request) error {
    if r == nil || r.Body == nil {
        return ErrInvalidRequest
    }
    var req CreateRequest
    if err := json.Decode(r.Body, &req); err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("decode: %w", err)
    }
    if req.Name == "" {
        return ErrInvalidRequest
    }
    return doWork(req)
}
```

## Extract function when a block has a comment describing it

A comment that describes what a block of code does is a signal that the block should be its own function with that name.

```go
// WRONG — comment says "validate input"; that's a function name
func handleCreateToken(ctx context.Context, req CreateTokenRequest) error {
    // validate input
    if req.Name == "" { return ErrEmptyName }
    if req.Permissions == 0 { return ErrEmptyPermissions }
    if req.ExpiresAt != nil && req.ExpiresAt.Before(time.Now()) { return ErrExpiredToken }

    // hash the token
    hash, err := argon2.Hash(rawToken)
    if err != nil { return err }

    // save to database
    return store.Insert(ctx, hash, req)
}

// RIGHT — each commented section is its own function
func handleCreateToken(ctx context.Context, req CreateTokenRequest) error {
    if err := validateCreateTokenRequest(req); err != nil { return err }
    hash, err := hashToken(rawToken)
    if err != nil { return err }
    return store.Insert(ctx, hash, req)
}

func validateCreateTokenRequest(req CreateTokenRequest) error {
    if req.Name == "" { return ErrEmptyName }
    if req.Permissions == 0 { return ErrEmptyPermissions }
    if req.ExpiresAt != nil && req.ExpiresAt.Before(time.Now()) { return ErrExpiredToken }
    return nil
}
```

## Prevent file hotspots — distribute change

A file that is changed in every PR AND has high complexity is a CodeScene "hotspot". Prevention:
1. Keep files ≤400 lines
2. Each file has one primary responsibility
3. If you touch a file 3 PRs in a row, it needs to be split

## Long parameter lists → options struct or builder

```go
// WRONG — 7 parameters; impossible to call without mistakes
func NewRedisSlider(host string, port int, password string, db int, timeout time.Duration, defaultRPM int64, orgOverrides map[uuid.UUID]int64) *RedisSlider

// RIGHT — options struct; fields are self-documenting; zero value = sane default
type RedisSliderConfig struct {
    Addr           string        // default: "localhost:6379"
    Password       string        // default: "" (no auth)
    DB             int           // default: 0
    Timeout        time.Duration // default: 5s
    DefaultRPM     int64         // default: 60
    OrgOverrides   map[uuid.UUID]int64 // default: nil (use DefaultRPM for all)
}
func NewRedisSlider(cfg RedisSliderConfig) *RedisSlider
```
